have not been seen since 1993  the first year the test was given for assessment purposes  The 15 year record of achievement is a tribute to the dedication of the faculty and the students of the department   When the Class of 1993 took the test  only 147 schools were in the comparison pool  In 2007  there were 553 schools in the pool  The table below shows the remarkable results our students have achieved  While the competition has gotten keener  VMI cadets have been able to compete with the best of them  Year Number of Schools Number of Students VMI Rank  percentile  Number of cadets in top 10  1993 147 8 319 95  9 out of 39 2006 513 109 982 95  7 out of 33 2007 553 143 349 95  8 out of 51 Spring 2007 Newsletter  AACSB Accreditation  Field Test BU  Mission Statement  New Faculty Faces  New Book Released  Faculty Research  Speakers  Engineering Initiative  Cadet Research  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  Class of 2005  Cadet Field Trip  Cadet Awards  Hinman Award  Stay Connected  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 